The article discusses the preparations for an Official State Visit in the State Dining Room of the White House. The event aims to bring together the United States and India, celebrating the strong ties and partnerships between the two countries. The article mentions that Prime Minister Modi is a vegetarian, so a vegetarian menu has been prepared by chef Nina Curtis, with the option to add fish. The dining room will be decorated in the colors of the Indian flag, with each table arrangement being warm and unique. After dinner, there will be performances by Grammy award winner Joshua Bell and the South Asian acapella group Penn Masala. The evening will conclude with guests walking across a moonlit lawn illuminated by glowing lanterns. The article also expresses gratitude to the White House residence staff, the social team, and the State Department staff for their hard work in organizing the event.